kube-controller-manager

Monitors the cluster state via the apiserver
and steers the cluster towards the desired state.

ex: monitors the status of the nodes, if any node is not reachabe, it will mark it as down ( after 40 secs ), schedules all the pods
to a different node.

ex: watches the number of pods running and matches with desired state

1.	Obtain desired state
2.	Observe current state
3.	Determine differences
4.	Reconcile differences
